    "created_at": "2015-03-18T16:55:47Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-03-18T16:55:47Z",
    "body": "We should have a library of common span operations that ensures the syntax contexts match.  These operations are necessarily partial; there's no sensible way to union spans from two different contexts. But we could introduce a \"span set\" or \"compound span\" to handle that.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
